  "levelSequence": [
    {
      "type": "story",
      "title": "The Diagonal Dilemma",
      "text": "Pip's number tiles have got themselves into a terrible muddle. They refuse to slide left or right like sensible tiles \u2014 instead they only swap diagonally, two at a time.\n\nMove Pip around the grid to position the 2\u00d72 swap cursor, then swipe diagonally to swap the corner tiles. Reach the target arrangement before you run out of moves!\n\nSome puzzles ask you to match a pattern. Others ask you to balance row sums. Either way, think before you swipe \u2014 each swap changes four tiles at once.",
      "image": "assets/rabbit_diagonal_swipes.png"
    },
